      • getPortInst

        public EDIFPortInst getPortInst(String name)
        Gets the port instance on this cell by pin name (EDIFPortInst.getName()). The port instances are stored in a sorted ArrayList, so worst case is O(log n).
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the port instance to get.
        Returns:
        The named port instance, or null if none found by that name.

      • getOrCreatePortInst

        public EDIFPortInst getOrCreatePortInst(String name)
        Gets the named EDIFPortInst or creates it (if correctly named) and returns it. If the port instance is to be created, it will not be connected to an EDIFNet.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the port instance to get.
        Returns:
        The existing or created port instance.

      • getPort

        public EDIFPort getPort(String name)
        Gets the port on the underlying cell type. It is the same as calling getCellType().getPort(name).
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the port to get.
        Returns:
        The port on the underlying cell type.
